<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Oh Litecoin</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing you can do is buy a bunch of=
 stock in some small publicly traded company and then put out a fake press =
release saying that Walmart Inc. is going to acquire that company. The stoc=
k will go up and you can sell your stock at a profit. Later Walmart and the=
 company will deny it and the stock will go back down, but if you=E2=80=99r=
e quick you can make a profit. Even later, the U.S. Securities and Exchange=
 Commission and federal prosecutors will come after you, but if you cover y=
our tracks well and live in a foreign country you might be okay. Anyway thi=
s is very much <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/250=
40090.270564/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMT=
UtMDYtMDQvZ3V5LXdoby1kaWQtYXZvbi1ob2F4LXdhcy10ZXJyaWJsZS1hdC1ob2F4ZXM/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB7299c4e3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> a thing</a> that people do occasionally in the U.S. st=
ock market.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another thing you can do is buy=
 a bunch of some cryptocurrency and then put out a fake press release sayin=
g that Walmart is going to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/25040090.270564/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjEtMDktMTMvd2FsbWFydC1kZW5pZXMtbGl0ZWNvaW4tcGFjdC1hZnRlci1ob2F4LWpvb=
HRzLWNyeXB0b2N1cnJlbmNpZXM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB139c2b74" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> =E2=80=9Cpartner with=
=E2=80=9D that cryptocurrency</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">Walmart Inc. said it hasn=E2=80=99t agreed to partner with Litecoin, re=
futing a statement earlier Monday that sent the cryptocurrency soaring.=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The statement released by GlobeNewswire=
 isn=E2=80=99t authentic, a Walmart representative confirmed to Bloomberg N=
ews. The company is in the process of trying to learn more about the releas=
e. The Litecoin Foundation said in a tweet that it hadn=E2=80=99t entered a=
 partnership with Walmart.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At 9:30 a.=
m. in New York, GlobeNewswire issued a statement saying that the world=E2=
=80=99s largest retailer had agreed to partner with Litecoin and accept the=
 cryptocurrency as payment. Litecoin had soared as much as 33% on the annou=
ncement, with other cryptocurrencies gaining as well. Litecoin erased almos=
t all of its gain, rising less than 1% at 12:12 p.m. in New York. Walmart s=
hares fell less than 1% to $145.01 after earlier trading in positive territ=
ory.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A spokesperson for Intrado, whic=
h operates GlobeNewswire, said the company is removing the release from its=
 website and is investigating the incident. Intrado distributes 200,000 pre=
ss releases per year, according to its website.</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">This is probably better than the corporate version, for a=
ll the reasons that crypto is generally attractive for crime. You can trade=
 your Litecoin anonymously, without going through a broker who will rat you=
 out to the SEC. You can trade your Litecoin any time; you don=E2=80=99t ha=
ve to wait for the markets to open to put out your press release. Also this=
 will just=C2=A0<em>work=C2=A0</em>really well: =E2=80=9CWalmart buys small=
 company=E2=80=9D is news, for the small company, but not that many people =
will care; =E2=80=9CWalmart does crypto thing=E2=80=9D is going to get more=
 attention, so people will definitely read your fake news and the price of =
Litecoin will go up.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, in the corporate=
 version, both Walmart and the fake target company will deny the story. In =
the crypto version, Walmart will probably be confused, and it=E2=80=99s not=
 even clear what it would mean for a cryptocurrency to deny a statement. A =
cryptocurrency is decentralized, etc.; there is not necessarily anyone who =
makes decisions for it and can say =E2=80=9Cthis is fake.=E2=80=9D Though i=
n this particular case there is someone who controls the @litecoin Twitter =
account and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/250400=
90.270564/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktM=
TMvY3J5cHRvY3VycmVuY2llcy1mYWxsLWFmdGVyLXdhbG1hcnQtc2F5cy1uby1wYWN0LXdpdGgt=
bGl0ZWNvaW4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6b0da14e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> confirmed the fake press release, aha=
hahaha</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A significant spike=
 in Litecoin followed quickly-debunked headlines that Walmart Inc., the wor=
ld=E2=80=99s largest retailer, had agreed to accept the cryptocurrency as a=
 payment mechanism at its stores. Litecoin=E2=80=99s own verified Twitter a=
ccount posted a link to the press release in a tweet that was later deleted=
. Charlie Lee, creator of Litecoin and managing director of the Litecoin Fo=
undation, described the tweet and press release as an =E2=80=9Cunfortunate =
situation=E2=80=9D in an interview with Bloomberg News.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe @litecoin handle, we have three people wh=
o control that and one of the people this morning, before I woke up, saw th=
e GlobeNewswire [press release] and saw Yahoo News posting it and CNBC post=
ing it and he thought it was true because he didn=E2=80=99t know better,=E2=
=80=9D Lee said. =E2=80=9CPretty soon after that he realized he had made a =
mistake, that it was fake and he deleted it.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I love it. If you run social media=C2=A0at Amalgama=
ted Widgets and you see a press release on the news saying =E2=80=9CWalmart=
 has bought Amalgamated Widgets,=E2=80=9D you are going to ask your boss =
=E2=80=9Cis this true=E2=80=9D before tweeting about it; that=E2=80=99s the=
 sort of thing you might expect to hear from your own company. If you run s=
ocial media for Litecoin just wave it all in, who knows, what does truth ev=
en mean.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Good times, good times. One assume=
s that this is illegal =E2=80=94=C2=A0surely it=E2=80=99s wire fraud? =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and that U.S. authorities will be looking for whoever did it; t=
his is just too fun a fraud not to prosecute. I do wonder if the=C2=A0<em>S=
EC=C2=A0</em>will go after this person (if they can find them) for=C2=A0<em=
>securities=C2=A0</em>fraud.[1] It=E2=80=99s not really securities fraud; L=
itecoin is not a security. But=C2=A0<em>Walmart=C2=A0</em>is, and its stock=
 moved on the news. If you accidentally manipulated Walmart=E2=80=99s stock=
 as part of your cunning plan to manipulate Litecoin, that might be enough =
for the SEC.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto=
