out what he=E2=80=99s up to at the SEC. Not like =E2=80=9Chere's a particul=
ar thing that I=E2=80=99m passionate about and my plan for new rulemaking,=
=E2=80=9D but more like =E2=80=9Chere is everything I=E2=80=99m thinking ab=
out with one sentence on each thing.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">If I had to give a broad summary, I guess I would go with =
=E2=80=9Cmore disclosure=E2=80=9D? That is a boring summary; pretty much ev=
ery speech and interview given by every SEC chair since the founding of the=
 agency could probably be summarized that way. Nonetheless I think it=E2=80=
=99s accurate. From the testimony:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">The security-based swaps market is not a large market compared to the f=
ixed income and equity markets, but it was at the core of the 2008 financia=
l crisis. More recently, total return swaps were at the heart of the failur=
e of Archegos Capital Management, a family office. =E2=80=A6.=C2=A0To allow=
 the Commission and the public to see aggregate positions, Congress under E=
xchange Act Section 10B gave us authority to mandate disclosure for positio=
ns in security-based swaps and related securities. I=E2=80=99ve asked staff=
 to think about potential rules for the Commission=E2=80=99s consideration =
under this authority. As the collapse of Archegos showed, this may be an im=
portant reform to consider</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today=E2=80=99s =
investors are looking for consistent, comparable, and decision-useful discl=
osures around climate risk, human capital, and cybersecurity. I=E2=80=99ve =
asked staff to develop proposals for the Commission=E2=80=99s consideration=
 on these potential disclosures. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
First, given the surge in special purpose acquisition companies (SPACs), I =
have asked staff for recommendations about enhancing disclosures in these i=
nvestments. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Further, we are worki=
ng to enhance disclosures with regard to how Chinese companies issue securi=
ties in the U.S. Chinese companies conducting business in certain industrie=
s, such as internet and technology, are prohibited from selling their owner=
ship stake to foreigners. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We=E2=
=80=99ve seen a growing number of funds market themselves as =E2=80=9Cgreen=
,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Csustainable,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Clow-carbon,=E2=80=9D and=
 so on. I=E2=80=99ve asked staff to consider ways to determine what informa=
tion stands behind those claims and how we can ensure that the public has t=
he information they need to understand their investment choices among these=
 types of funds.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=
 is so pleasing because it is simultaneously the U.S.=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25040090.270564/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDEtMTUvaXQtcy1ub3QtaW5z=
